<h2>Why This Is Important For Me</h2>
<p>For some insane reason I've felt guilty for using PHP frameworks, but almost 90% of the time they answer the problem that I'm trying to solve. For example, this very blog. I've struggled with whether I should create a blog engine from scratch. Why? Because using a PHP framework feels like cheating. But good ol Rasmus explains that I shouldn't because I've answered the problem that I was trying to solve. Having a blog. While the whole talk is very good that particular part is really good.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:40:"I Feel Better About Using PHP Frameworks";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:6:"closed";s:11:"ping_status";s:6:"closed";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:32:"feel-better-using-php-frameworks";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2014-02-06 02:52:38";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2014-02-06 02:52:38";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:29:"http://bryansiegel.com/?p=601";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}}